### DevForge / ZastraBackend API Tests
# To use this file:
# 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code OR use IntelliJ IDEA
# 2. Click "Send Request" above each request.
# 3. Important: Run the login request first to get the {{auth_token}} populated automatically (VS Code handles @token, or copy it manually).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1
@pythonUrl = http://localhost:8000
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### ====================================================
### 1. AUTHENTICATION
### ====================================================

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser123",
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login (Run this to get the Auth Token!)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ====================================================
### 2. PROFILE
### ====================================================

### Get current user profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update current user profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Test User",
  "bio": "I am a backend developer.",
  "targetRoles": ["Backend Engineer", "Java Developer"]
}

### ====================================================
### 3. INTEGRATIONS & EXTERNAL SYNC
### ====================================================

### Get integration status
GET {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Sync GitHub Activity (Links the Github Account)
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/github/sync
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pulkit1245"
}

### Sync LeetCode Activity
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/leetcode/sync
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pulkit1245"
}

### ====================================================
### 4. PROJECTS
### ====================================================

### Create a new project
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Zastra Advanced Anti-Cheat Tracker",
  "description": "Built using Spring Boot, Kafka, and Python",
  "techStack": ["Java", "Spring Boot", "Python", "FastAPI"],
  "link": "https://github.com/pulkit1245/zastra"
}

### Get all projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ====================================================
### 5. ACTIVITY & STATISTICS
### ====================================================

### Get global activity metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/activity/global
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get GitHub generic activity metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/activity/github
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get contest rankings (Leetcode/Codeforces etc.)
GET {{baseUrl}}/activity/contest
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ====================================================
### 6. GAMIFICATION
### ====================================================

### Get Gamification Summary (Rank, badges, XP)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gamification/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Leaderboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/gamification/leaderboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ====================================================
### 7. PUBLIC PORTFOLIO
### ====================================================

### View a user's generated public portfolio
GET {{baseUrl}}/portfolio/public/testuser123
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get directory of users
GET {{baseUrl}}/portfolio/directory
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ====================================================
### 8. PYTHON MICROSERVICE (Runs directly)
### ====================================================

### Health Check
GET {{pythonUrl}}/health

### Scrape GitHub Data
GET {{pythonUrl}}/github/pulkit1245

### Scrape LeetCode Data
GET {{pythonUrl}}/leetcode/pulkit1245
